text: Radosław Kanach (born 3 April 1999 in Rzeszów) is a Polish footballer who plays as a midfielder for Sandecja Nowy Sącz, on loan from KS Cracovia. ==Club career== Kanach started his career with III liga side Stal Rzeszów, where he made 33 appearances over 2 seasons. He signed for Ekstraklasa side Cracovia in June 2016. His first involvement with the first team was in a mid-season training camp in Spain; where he played in matches against Chinese side Yanbian Funde and Moldovan side Dacia Chișinău. He made his league debut in a 4–1 loss to Wisła Płock, picking up a yellow card in the 9th minute. ==International career== In 2013, while a player with Stal Rzeszów, Kanach was called up to the Polish under-15 side.
